{"level":50,"time":1776488628543,"pid":997002,"hostname":"interstellar","module":"db.sqlite","err":{"type":"Error","message":"database or disk is full","stack":"SQLiteError: database or disk is full\n    at run (unknown)\n    at #run (bun:sqlite:185:20)\n    at query (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/db/adapters/sqlite.ts:87:29)\n    at query (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/db/connection.ts:111:26)\n    at createWorkflowEvent (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/db/workflow-events.ts:45:16)\n    at <anonymous> (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/workflows/store-adapter.ts:49:31)\n    at executeNodeInternal (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/workflows/src/dag-executor.ts:961:12)\n    at async <anonymous> (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/workflows/src/dag-executor.ts:2754:28)\n    at async executeDagWorkflow (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/workflows/src/dag-executor.ts:2428:40)\n    at async executeWorkflow (unknown)\n    at async workflowRunCommand (unknown)\n    at async main (unknown)\n    at processTicksAndRejections (native:7:39)","code":"SQLITE_FULL","errno":13,"byteOffset":-1},"sql":"INSERT INTO remote_agent_workflow_events (id, workflow_run_id, event_type, step_index, step_name, data)\n       VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)","params":["5e35b5b8-2c48-4cb9-bebd-5d69433bf0af","615101356ca6d68ccb8a95eec2aac1e8","tool_called",null,"code-review","{\"tool_name\":\"Write\",\"tool_input\":{\"file_path\":\"/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/615101356ca6d68ccb8a95eec2aac1e8/review/code-review-findings.md\",\"content\":\"# Code Review Findings: PR (Fix #279 — Task Checkboxes Sidebar Toggle)\\n\\n**Reviewer**: code-review-agent\\n**Date**: 2026-04-18T00:00:00Z\\n**Files Reviewed**: 2 (`frontend/src/store.ts`, `frontend/src/components/ThingCard.tsx`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe implementation is minimal, targeted, and correct. Both required branches of `updateThing` in `store.ts` are updated to remove inactive things from the `things` array, and the `ThingCard.tsx` `translateY` animation is strengthened. The changes exactly match the plan spec.\\n\\n**Verdict**: APPROVE\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Findings\\n\\n### Finding 1: `detailThing` updated but not cleared on deactivation (intentional, informational)\\n\\n**Severity**: LOW\\n**Category**: style\\n**Location**: `frontend/src/store.ts:894`, `frontend/src/store.ts:904`\\n\\n**Issue**:\\nWhen `updates.active === false`, the item is correctly removed from `things`, but `detailThing` is still updated to the now-inactive object. This means if the detail panel is open for the task being completed, it will continue to display the inactive thing.\\n\\n**Evidence**:\\n```typescript\\n// store.ts:890-895 (202 branch)\\nset(state => ({\\n  things: updates.active === false\\n    ? state.things.filter(t => t.id !== id)\\n    : state.things.map(t => t.id === id ? { ...t, ...updates } as Thing : t),\\n  detailThing: state.detailThing?.id === id ? { ...state.detailThing, ...updates } as Thing : state.detailThing,\\n  //           ^^^ detailThing kept, even when active: false\\n}))\\n```\\n\\n**Why This Matters**:\\nThis is intentional per the plan (\\\"detailThing deliberately keeps the updated (now inactive) object so the detail panel doesn't crash if it's open\\\"). It is NOT a bug. Flagged for informational awareness in case future reviewers question it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### Fix Suggestions\\n\\nNot applicable — this is intentional behavior. No change needed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Finding 2: Animation timing aligns correctly but relies on 100ms slack\\n\\n**Severity**: LOW\\n**Category**: style\\n**Location**: `frontend/src/components/ThingCard.tsx:39`\\n\\n**Issue**:\\nThe `handleCheckbox` waits 600ms before calling `updateThing`, while the CSS transition is `duration-500` (500ms). The 100ms gap is intentional slack to let the animation finish. This is correct, but the relationship between the two numbers is implicit — a future developer could change the CSS duration without adjusting the timeout.\\n\\n**Evidence**:\\n```typescript\\n// ThingCard.tsx:34-41\\nconst handleCheckbox = async (e: React.MouseEvent) => {\\n  e.stopPropagation()\\n  if (completing) return\\n  setCompleting(true)\\n  // Give animation time to play before the item disappears from the list\\n  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 600))  // ← 600ms\\n  await updateThing(thing.id, { active: false })\\n}\\n```\\n```typescript\\n// ThingCard.tsx:45\\nclassName=\\\"px-3 py-1 transition-all duration-500\\\"  // ← 500ms\\n```\\n\\n**Why This Matters**:\\nLow risk. The comment on line 38 documents the intent. The coupling is acceptable at this scale.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#### Fix Suggestions\\n\\n| Option | Approach | Pros | Cons |\\n|--------|----------|------|------|\\n| A | Keep as-is (status quo) | Simple, matches plan exactly | Implicit coupling between 600 and 500 |\\n| B | Extract constant: `const ANIMATION_MS = 500` and use `ANIMATION_MS + 100` in setTimeout | Makes coupling explicit | Slight over-engineering for a one-off |\\n\\n**Recommended**: Option A\\n\\n**Reasoning**: The comment already documents the intent. Extracting a constant adds complexity without meaningful benefit at this component scale. CLAUDE.md says don't add abstractions for one-time operations.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Statistics\\n\\n| Severity | Count | Auto-fixable |\\n|----------|-------|--------------|\\n| CRITICAL | 0 | 0 |\\n| HIGH | 0 | 0 |\\n| MEDIUM | 0 | 0 |\\n| LOW | 2 | 0 |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## CLAUDE.md Compliance\\n\\n| Rule | Status | Notes |\\n|------|--------|-------|\\n| Fix only what bead describes | PASS | Changes limited to `store.ts` and `ThingCard.tsx` exactly as scoped |\\n| Schema changes use additive SQL migrations | N/A | No backend/DB changes |\\n| PRs must reference GitHub issue | PASS | Plan specifies `Fixes #279` |\\n| Screenshot tests: run, update, inspect | PENDING | Cannot verify from code; task 3 instructs this — reviewer should confirm screenshots were updated and inspected |\\n| No speculative abstractions | PASS | No helpers or utilities added beyond the task |\\n| No backwards-compatibility hacks | PASS | None present |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Patterns Referenced\\n\\n| File | Lines | Pattern |\\n|------|-------|---------|\\n| `frontend/src/store.ts` | 890-895 | 202-branch `set()` call — `updates.active === false` ternary applied correctly |\\n| `frontend/src/store.ts` | 900-905 | 200-branch `set()` call — same ternary applied correctly |\\n| `frontend/src/components/ThingCard.tsx` | 36 | `if (completing) return` guard prevents double-fire on rapid clicks |\\n| `frontend/src/components/ThingCard.tsx` | 45-46 | `transition-all duration-500` + inline style pattern for completing animation |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Positive Observations\\n\\n- **Both store branches updated**: The plan explicitly flagged \\\"offline 202 branch missed\\\" as a MED-likelihood risk. The implementation correctly handles both the 202 offline optimistic branch and the 200 API success branch — no single-path-only fix.\\n- **`filter` is idempotent**: If the item is already absent from `things` (race or duplicate call), `filter` is a no-op. Safe.\\n- **`if (completing) return` guard**: Correctly prevents double-invocation on rapid clicks without needing `useRef` or other machinery.\\n- **No new imports, no new abstractions**: Changes are surgical and scoped exactly to the two lines described in the plan.\\n- **`translateY(20px)` is proportionate**: Large enough to communicate directionality, small enough not to cause layout jank before removal.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Metadata\\n\\n- **Agent**: code-review-agent\\n- **Timestamp**: 2026-04-18T00:00:00Z\\n- **Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/615101356ca6d68ccb8a95eec2aac1e8/review/code-review-findings.md`\\n\"}}"],"msg":"db.sqlite_query_failed"}
